    • Method Detail

      • checkUniqueParticipant

        public static boolean checkUniqueParticipant(java.lang.String participantName)
        checkUniqueParticipant is a method that will determine whether or not a certain participant name is taken upon sign up or log in. When you sign up, we need this method to be false, to ensure that there are no other names in the server and that the unique quality is satisfied. When you log in, the method should be true, to ensure that there is a participant stored in the server and its information can be retrieved for use in the app.
        Parameters:
        participantName -
        Returns:
        true if name is found

      • updateSingletonList

        public static void updateSingletonList()
        updateSingletonList will attempt to pull the most up to date list of participants from the elastic server in attempt to try and log in to the app as some participant that is already registered. This makes it so that the app user will be able to login from any phone so long an internet connection is there.
